(only sysop, only DOS and Windows, init.bcm)
Syntax: Summertime [ 0 | 1 ]
(default: 1)

Defines if the automatic summer time function of OpenBCM should be used or
not. A value of "1" is normally used in western europa. If the system is
used in a country that has no summer time, a value of "0" is the best choice.

Note: this value is not intended to be used to switch between summer and
