Syntax: U(SERS) [*] | [<call>]

Lists the users of the BBS. There will be shown what the users are just doing:

Idle     user is doing nothing, he only stares at the screen (hi)
Read     user is reading a mail from the BBS
Send     user is sending a mail to the BBS
Cmd      a DOS operation (runutil program) is executed
Search   search process (DIR, LIST or CHECK)
FwdTX    S&F sending to another BBS
FwdRX    S&F receiving from another BBS
You      youself

If a user is shown as "Idle" you can send him a message with TALK command.

